column5: Rob do you know this guy??????????? Sorry, I cant stop laughing.    Thanks Jacques. It is a nice slab. He and his girlfriend got one last year too.This one beat it by 1/2 an inch.
Wow, nice fish! Not easy to get on them on Simcoe! Congrats! Dave
HOLY Crappie.....   Nice fish...huge!
wow that s a huge slab of a crappie!  Cheers!
Now that's a slab. Makes my 13 inchers at first ice look tiny!
Heres a few pics of this huge fish. Turns out,he will be having it skin mounted. I would do the same.        When I told him about the responses,his chest seem to grow 10 times.LOL
I remember 8 years ago, I could fill a pail with crappie every night (never did, because I dont eat much fish, but others certainly did) Now, I get a few a year
Steve,  I remember when they came into the marina years back. It was nuts and a slaughter.
Just took this pic. It was 16 and a half long and the girth was the same. HUGE
and why the heck isnt he on a team???
I,ll need to talk to the boy. He,s fishing all the time. Just like I USE to do.LOL That fish would feed a family of 4.LOL
Simcoe county crappie or lake simcoe crappie I never get crappie through the ice on Lake Simcoe nice going
lake simcoe crappie I showed him all he needs to know.As for you,I show you, what I want you to know.LOL
hey  who let you back on here anyways
Wow......what a pig!!!  That is one fish I've NEVER caught out of simcoe!! They  elude me averytime I try!!!  Sinker
I found the key. It was in the snow drift.
Maybe during a duck hunt,I,ll tell ya Shane.   a I know,you have offered up before bud.
That's a huge slab! Did it have numbers painted on the side! You could land a plane on that thing! Congrats! HH
Wow, what a beast.  Is he sharing that with you for dinner  Joey
Check my new post J. That was our dinner.LOL
Great fish!  What ever your doing keep it going.  Fish of that size.   Wow!
Awesome crappie !!!! oh my god,i can taste that huge fish right now !!!   great job...cheers
Thats a huge Crappie! Congrats to your boy misfish!
Did not realize they got that large. Must have had a bit of a tug bringing that one up.
That sure is a nice slab Ryan got
What a beautiful specimen
My son or the fish?
Great fish!....where are these guys in the summer?  (I know: swimming)   forrest
WOW!  and Oh so yummy!
Ryan is one great guy to fish with and seems to always land some nice fishing. To bad his dad is not the same
WOW real huge slab for sure.... Congratulations to your son  Thanks Brian for sharing Jacques
Oh you did not just say that? Are you calling me out ?????????????  Who do you think taught/showed  my son???????????????????  The legacy lives on.
I think Rob showed ryan all he knows and yes i'm calling you out get your ass in gear and come fishing for the love of god lol
